Lucky #7! Stoked to be able to share this image today! The Tarpon Cover has been a goal of mine since I started shooting for @swsportsman 5 years ago! Very appreciative of them for allowing me to showcase my work through their magazine!

What a trip this was down to Costa Rica! Super thankful I was able to be connected with @506_outdoors through my good friend @backwaterflyfishing! We had a hell of a time and I will forever remember all the tarpon we raised that week! Unreal. 

I can’t thank the people that continue to support me enough. Though times are tougher nowadays trying to keep steady gigs coming in with everyone and their brother wanting to be a photographer..it is extremely important to have a core group of people that continue to push me to be better with their unwavering positivity, love, and appreciation for my dreams and goals and for that I truly thank you.

In closing I want to thank @recreationspecialist for wrangling this beast of a tarpon..without him this shot wouldn’t have happened! But also @el_flyflinger86 for fighting this monster on fly and giving us the opportunity for me to capture this moment for us all! It’s always a team effort and I feel that it is important to share that..without them..this cover wouldn’t be possible and without Jesse I wouldn’t have been on the trip! It is just as much theirs as it is mine. I am and will forever be appreciative for the week spent with Jesse, Court, @macelliottmedia, @j_bugz85, @beachbandit506, and Aaron! I look forward to the next time we are all together again! 

Until next time. Let’s go capture #8

𝐑𝐞𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭 𝐛𝐚𝐜𝐤: (an excerpt from a story I told in my podcast last week)

It’s pretty wild to me how much moments in our lives can be a staple of a time you will never forget. I often think about things this way and I always try to take in these  moments and cherish the times I have with loved ones. It is easy to get caught up in our daily lives and not take the time to appreciate things that really bring us joy. We are often too busy to see the moments that mean a lot to us until they are gone, but, being able to sit in a moment and reflect on good times you have shared with your family and friends is a great way to think and a great way to live your life.

That was an emotional night for me and I’m not ashamed to say as a man tears were flowin in the deer stand after I harvested my 10pt behind my grandparents house. I sat in the moment and took in what it meant to me for a solid thirty minutes or so thanking God and my grandparents for allowing me the opportunity to come 𝐟𝐮𝐥𝐥 𝐜𝐢𝐫𝐜𝐥𝐞 on a moment I thought about years prior and knew was coming for quite some time. I truly appreciated being able to be alone in this moment while in my thoughts. It allowed me to live in it without distraction and to think about what my grandparents and this land meant to me and my family. I will always be thankful for that moment and the family traditions that allow us to put ourselves back in great times in our lives.

Take the time to live in the moment when surrounded by people you truly appreciate. 

Have a great Thursday. 👊

@whiskeyandwhitetails 

#jhodgeproductions #whiskeyandwhitetails #familytraditions #deerhunting #hunting #seewhatisee #mystory #liveoutsidethebox

Does catching big jacks off the beach, monster bonefish in the Bahamas and baby tarpon in the everglades spark your interest? Then you better hang on! THE RUNAROUND is a wild project I filmed with my good buddy @j.hodgeproductions as we ran from Jensen Beach, to Walkers Cay, and back to the Everglades all in a 10 day trip we will never forget! So stoked to see this film in the lineup for the 2024 @flyfilmfest! BE SURE TO SMASH THAT SHARE BUTTON AND HELP GET THE WORD OUT!
